清華大學暑期密集華語課程-初級華語一&初級華語二 (National Tsing Hua University Summer Intensive Chinese Program- Basic Mandarin I&II)














清華大學暑期密集華語課程-初級華語一
(National Tsing Hua University Summer Intensive Chinese Program- 
Basic Mandarin I)
* 校內選課時間: June 29th 2012起 至July 5th 2012 
  Registration Date: 6/29/2012 to 7/5/2012  
- For those who has already enrolled at NTHU, please register through the academic and course information page under the Division of Curriculum website.
 - For new students, please reply with the admission letter to the Office of International Affairs   
* 校外人士選課請至 http://exten.web.nthu.edu.tw/files/11-1154-3497.php (not available yet)
  For people who is not a student of NTHU, please register through the link above, and the course fee for non-NTHU students will be NTD$2500 /per credit, three credits total. 
  (校內或校外修畢皆可抵三學分及申請學分/時數證明,若開學後欲繼續修習華
  語課程,可直接銜接初級華語 II 及初級華語 III )
 
Student who has taken the intensive program in the summer will receive 3 credits at NTHU and a certificate of totals hours of the course. 
And you may take Mandarin Basic II and Mandarin Basic III in the Fall semester after taking the summer course.
 
􀂾 預期目標：
1.協助外籍學生在大學或研究所之課程學習及在台生活。
2.具備 初級華語I 聽說讀寫四技能,可銜接101學年度上學期(初級華語 II )之課程。
3.學習基本生活用語以適應全中文環境。
􀂾 Objectives of the Summer Intensive Program:

To assist foreign students in facing school life and blending into the new environment.
Basic listening and speaking skills are taught in the courses, along with some more skills in basic Chinese such as reading and writing. 
This program is designed to engage with the intermediate Chinese course, students who is interested in continuing Chinese course can take Basic Mandarin II and III in the 2012 Fall semester.

 
􀂾 課程對象：
1.本校母語非華語之外籍學生(華語程度:零起點-初級)
  (開放校外人士選修)。
2.領取獎學金之外籍生可抵華語文學習時數。
􀂾 Prospective Students:

All foreign students at NTNU (Beginner to Basic Chinese skills)  
This program also opened to Non- NTNU students who is interested in studying Chinese.
International students with NTNU scholarships are required to take Mandarin courses, this program can compensate for the hours required by the Office of International Affairs.

 
􀂾 課程教材：
新版實用視聽華語第一冊(1~8課)及教師自編教材講義
􀂾 Teaching Materials:
Practical Audio-visual Chinese(I)，Zhengzhong Publication. (New Edition) L1 ~ L8
Supplementary Handouts 
 
􀂾 課程內容：
1.語音/漢語拼音 -15 hrs
2.綜合課(詞彙/語法/對話) -90 hrs
3.基本電腦中文輸入法 -3 hrs
4.文化課程 -9 hrs
5.基礎會話 -9 hrs
􀂾 Curriculum:
1. Phonics/Pinyin -15hrs
2. Comprehensive class (Vocabulary/Grammar/Dialogue) -90hrs
3. Basic computer typing skills in Chinese -3hrs
4. Culture class -9hrs
5. Basic conversation class -9hrs 
 
** 密集華語課程為期六週（初級華語I - 8/6 ~ 9/14) ,週一至週五上午9:00-12:00為綜合課,
   每週二、四下午1:00-4:00另安排正音/輔導補強課程、文化體驗及會話課程。
The Summer Intensive Chinese Program is a 6 weeks (Mandarin Basic I- 8/6 ~ 9/14)   course.
The Summer Intensive Chinese Program will last 6 weeks, five days a week:
9:00~12:00 on Monday, Wednesday and Friday 
9:00~12:00, 13:00~16:00 on Tuesday and Thursday. (with conversation and culture classes in the afternoon)
 
初級華語 I (Mandarin Basic I )
8/6/2012~ 9/14/2012 
Monday – Friday  9am~12pm
Tuesday& Thursday 1pm~4pm (conversation & culture classes)
 
初級華語二
(National Tsing Hua University Summer Intensive Chinese Program- 
Basic Mandarin I)
* 校內選課時間: June 29th 2012起 至July 5th 2012 
Registration Date: 6/29/2012 to 7/5/2012 
- For those who has already enrolled at NTHU, please register through the academic and course information page under the Division of Curriculum website.
- For new students, please reply with the admission letter to the Office of International Affairs 
* 校外人士選課請至 http://exten.web.nthu.edu.tw/files/11-1154-3497.php (not available yet)
For people who is not a student of NTHU, please register through the link above, and the course fee for non-NTHU students will be NTD$2500 /per credit, three credits total. 
(校內或校外修畢皆可抵三學分及申請學分/時數證明,若開學後欲繼續修習華
語課程,可直接銜接初級華語 III )
 
Student who has taken the intensive program in the summer will receive 3 credits at NTHU and a certificate of totals hours of the course. 
And you may take Mandarin Basic III in the Fall semester after taking the summer course.
 
􀂾 預期目標：
1.協助外籍學生在大學或研究所之課程學習及在台生活。
2.具備 初級華語I&II 聽說讀寫四技能,可銜接101學年度上學期(初級華語 III )之課程。
3.學習基本生活用語以適應全中文環境。
􀂾 Objectives of the Summer Intensive Program:

To assist foreign students in facing school life and blending into the new environment.
Basic listening and speaking skills are taught in the courses, along with some more skills in basic Chinese such as reading and writing. 
This program is designed to engage with the intermediate Chinese course, students who is interested in continuing Chinese course can take Basic Mandarin II and III in the 2012 Fall semester.

 
􀂾 課程對象：
1.本校母語非華語之外籍學生(華語程度:零起點-初級)
(開放校外人士選修)。
2.領取獎學金之外籍生可抵華語文學習時數。
􀂾 Prospective Students:

All foreign students at NTNU (Beginner to Basic Chinese skills) 
This program also opened to Non- NTNU students who is interested in studying Chinese.
International students with NTNU scholarships are required to take Mandarin courses, this program can compensate for the hours required by the Office of International Affairs.

 
􀂾 課程教材：
新版實用視聽華語第一冊(9~14課)、實用視聽華語第二冊(1~4課)及教師自編教材講義
􀂾 Teaching Materials:
Practical Audio-visual Chinese(I)，Zhengzhong Publication. (New Edition) L9 ~ L14 & 
Practical Audio-visual Chinese(II)，Zhengzhong Publication. (New Edition) L1 ~ L4
Supplementary Handouts 
 
􀂾 課程內容：
1.語音/漢語拼音 -15 hrs
2.綜合課(詞彙/語法/對話) -90 hrs
3.基本電腦中文輸入法 -3 hrs
4.文化課程 -9 hrs
5.基礎會話 -9 hrs
􀂾 Curriculum:
1. Phonics/Pinyin -15hrs
2. Comprehensive class (Vocabulary/Grammar/Dialogue) -90hrs
3. Basic computer typing skills in Chinese -3hrs
4. Culture class -9hrs
5. Basic conversation class -9hrs 
 
** 密集華語課程為期六週（初級華語I - 6/25 ~ 8/3) ,週一至週五上午9:00-12:00為綜合課,
每週二、四下午1:00-4:00另安排正音/輔導補強課程、文化體驗及會話課程。
The Summer Intensive Chinese Program is a 6 weeks (Mandarin Basic II- 6/25 ~ 8/3) course.
The Summer Intensive Chinese Program will last 6 weeks, five days a week:
9:00~12:00 on Monday, Wednesday and Friday 
9:00~12:00, 13:00~16:00 on Tuesday and Thursday. (with conversation and culture classes in the afternoon)
 
初級華語 II (Mandarin Basic II )
6/25/2012~ 8/3/2012 
Monday – Friday 9am~12pm
Tuesday& Thursday 1pm~4pm (conversation & culture classes)
 
 
 


















